Description: Oval handle sliver of a RHodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 188a, 12? Name Themison. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0630.26.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1063)
